annotationA: Uncharacterized protein, isoform A; Selenocysteine methyltransferase activity; S-adenosylmethionine-homocysteine S-methyltransferase activity
annotationB: S-adenosylmethionine synthase; Catalyzes the formation of S-adenosylmethionine from methionine and ATP. The reaction comprises two steps that are both catalyzed by the same enzyme: formation of S-adenosylmethionine (AdoMet) and triphosphate, and subsequent hydrolysis of the triphosphate
